From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 01:41:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 28/41] web-app: submit single-input prompt dialogs with Enter
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Prompt-style dialogs with one text input (edit profile display name,
edit contact name, account private tag) did nothing on Enter — the OK
button had to be clicked. Wrap their bodies in a form with the footer
OK button as the submit button (the same pattern EditGroupNameDialog
already uses), so Enter in the input confirms the dialog like a native
prompt() does. Enter in the profile status textarea still inserts a
newline (implicit form submission only fires from inputs).
---
 .../EditPrivateTagDialog.tsx                  | 38 +++++++++---------
 .../dialogs/EditProfileDialog/index.tsx       | 10 ++---
 .../components/dialogs/ViewProfile/menu.tsx   | 40 ++++++++++---------
 3 files changed, 44 insertions(+), 44 deletions(-)

diff --git a/packages/frontend/src/components/AccountListSidebar/EditPrivateTagDialog.tsx b/packages/frontend/src/components/AccountListSidebar/EditPrivateTagDialog.tsx
